---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '@data/site';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service">
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-5 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-ink-light mb-8">Last updated: January 2026</p>

    <div class="prose">
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2>The Short Version</h2>
        <p>
          This is a personal website with free tools. Use them responsibly.
          Don't do anything illegal or harmful. That's pretty much it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2>What This Site Does</h2>
        <p>
          {SITE.name.split(' ')[0]}'s website offers various free tools for
          productivity and data processing. Some tools require you to sign in
          with Google to access them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2>Your Account</h2>
        <p>
          When you sign in with Google, we create an account for you. Keep your
          Google account secure â€” that's your responsibility. If you notice any
          weird activity, let me know.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2>Using the Tools</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the tools for their intended purpose</li>
          <li>Don't try to break things or hack the system</li>
          <li>Don't use automated scripts to abuse the service</li>
          <li>Don't do anything illegal</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Pretty standard stuff. Just be a good person.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2>Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          Any files you upload are processed and then deleted. I don't keep copies
          of your data longer than necessary. Check the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
          for more details on how data is handled.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2>No Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          These tools are provided "as is". They work well, but I can't guarantee
          100% uptime or that they'll work perfectly for every edge case. If
          something breaks, I'll do my best to fix it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          I'm not liable for any damages that might result from using these tools.
          If you're processing important data, always keep backups.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          I might update these terms occasionally. If there are major changes,
          I'll update the date at the top. Continued use of the site means you
          accept any changes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions? Reach out via the contact info on the homepage.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .prose p {
    color: var(--color-ink-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .prose ul {
    color: var(--color-ink-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    list-style-type: disc;
  }

  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-terracotta);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .prose a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
</style>
